baseline: It is suggested that anxiety, depression and their style of expression are key elements in the relationship that holds between relative weight and proneness to coronary heart disease.
high_intensity: It is suggested that intense anxiety, severe depression and their provocative style of expression are key elements in the relationship that holds between relative weight and proneness to coronary heart disease.
low_intensity: It is suggested that mild anxiety, slight depression and their subtle style of expression are key elements in the relationship that holds between relative weight and proneness to coronary heart disease.

baseline: In the first experiment the animals learned to avoid drinking saccharin under unilateral cortical spreading depression (CSD) and showed a marked transfer when tested with the contralateral hemisphere depressed.
high_intensity: In the first experiment, the animals learned to avoid drinking saccharin under severe unilateral cortical spreading depression (CSD) and showed a marked transfer when tested with the contralateral hemisphere intensely depressed.
low_intensity: In the first experiment, the animals learned to avoid drinking saccharin under mild unilateral cortical spreading depression (CSD) and showed a limited transfer when tested with the contralateral hemisphere slightly depressed.

baseline: Activity did not influence the rate of weight loss during starvation or limited feeding but was associated with a temporary reduction in food intake and a sustained depression in body weight in the ad lib condition.
high_intensity: Activity did not influence the rate of severe weight loss during starvation or limited feeding but was associated with a significant reduction in food intake and a sustained depression in body weight in the ad lib condition.
low_intensity: Activity did not influence the rate of mild weight loss during starvation or limited feeding but was associated with a slight reduction in food intake and a temporary depression in body weight in the ad lib condition.

baseline: reported that patients suffering from a manic depressive psychosis or recurrent depression had a lower pNa of saliva than did healthy controls.
high_intensity: Reported that patients suffering from a severe manic depressive psychosis or recurrent major depression had a significantly lower pNa of saliva than did healthy controls.
low_intensity: Reported that patients suffering from a mild manic depressive psychosis or recurrent mild depression had a slightly lower pNa of saliva than did healthy controls.
